Kenyan Remittances Surged 53% to $79.6 Million in August

-- B y   S a r a h   M c G r e g o r
-- 
2011-09-16T13:14:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/kenyan-remittances-surged-53-to-79-6-million-in-august-1-.html
Kenyan remittances from abroad
surged 53 percent from a year earlier to a record $79.6 million
in August, the Central Bank of Kenya said.  Money sent home from Kenyans living abroad in the first
eight months of the year climbed 39 percent to $558.9 million,
the Nairobi-based central bank said on its website today. About
78 percent of the money arriving in August came from  North
America  and  Europe , it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sarah McGregor in Nairobi at 
 smcgregor5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net . 